<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-02-23T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-02-23T19:00:00-05:00" n="789" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d789">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A4d/126: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-02-23T19:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">February 23,
                                        1926—7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>46. I am temporarily withholding reply of the Department in view of
                            urgent request of Chinese Minister for delay. He hopes to obtain
                            permission shortly to withdraw note. I expect to be able, if he
                            succeeds, to authorize you to return the note from the Foreign Office
                            unanswered.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>